/minnesota/mahnomen/", "3/united states/minnesota/mahnomen/mahnomen/"], "contributor": ["minnesota historical society; saint paul, mn"], "date": "1930-09-05", "dates": ["1930-09-05"], "description": ["Mahnomen Pioneer j z Volume 26 WASHINGTON CORRESPONDENCE Bankers and Capitalists Rule Amer ica According to Former Am bassador Gerard According to former Ambassador James W Gerard fiftynine Amer icans rule America He does not in clude in the list the President of the United States or even a Senator The only Cabinet officer mentioned is Secretary of the Treasury Mellon Mr Gerard believes that real power in America rests with bankers and capitalists and his list is made up of men who have great wealth at their command and who rule by virtue of their ability Gerard reverts to the old philosophy that it takes money to make the mare go As for his list well it is additional proof of the prewar suspicion that Gerard is an imaginative sort of a good fellow Pennsylvania Improves For generations Pennsylvania could be counted upon to obey its masters of politics But independ ent thought and an improved class of statesmenship have produced good results in recent years Vare came very nearly turning the Key stone State back into its old politi cal ways and Grundy bobbed up representing organized business The recent decision of the Supreme Court of Pennsylvania in"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-07-10T20:19:27.243Z", "group": ["ndnp/mnhi", "minnesota-historical-society-saint-paul-mn-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83016586/1930-09-05/ed-1/?sp=1", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mnhi:batch_mnhi_guildenstern_ver01:data:sn83016586:00542865167:1930090501:0299/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=272&w=194", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mnhi:batch_mnhi_guildenstern_ver01:data:sn83016586:00542865167:1930090501:0299/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=544&w=389", "https://tile.loc.gov/i